 R‚Üê‚çôGitIgnore ‚çôRA;‚çôCMD;‚çôPDIR;‚çôTEMP;‚çôTIE;‚çôWS

‚çù - Mark a file within the parent directory as a file that should not
‚çù   be managed by ]Git.  The first time this call is run for a
‚çù   repository, a "gitignore" file is created in the repository to
‚çù   keep track of the ignored files.  Subsequent ]Git Ignore calls
‚çù   will update the existing gitignore file.  [Filename] includes the extension
‚çù   but not filepath required.  After using this call, the gitignore file will
‚çù   need to be added, commited and then pushed via ]Git Add, ]Git Commit and ]Git Push.
‚çù
‚çù   Returns the updated contents of the .gitignore file
‚çù
‚çù   Otherwise, returns an error message.
‚çù
‚çù - [TLDR: Tell git not to track a file]
‚çù
‚çù NOTE: If file already being tracked (i.e. committed at least once),
‚çù then .gitignore will not stop Git from tracking it (will need to remove it
‚çù first then add it again)

 (‚çôRA ‚çôTEMP ‚çôPDIR)‚Üê‚çôRA

 ‚çù Build ‚éïCMD argument to pass to ‚àÜ_COMMAND
 ‚çù Note >> appends the file
 ‚çôCMD‚Üê'cd ',‚çôPDIR,' && echo ',‚çôRA,' >> .gitignore'
‚çù Run cmd call:
 3 ‚éïCMD ‚çôCMD
‚çù Read contents of .gitignore
 ‚çôCMD‚Üê'type .gitignore'
 R‚Üê‚çôTEMP ‚çôCOMMAND ‚çôPDIR ‚çôCMD
